 origin"]}, {"name": "dicomity.group.DicomStack.sort_images_by_location", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reporting", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Sort a series of Dicom images by their slice locations and calculate\nadditional image parameters\n\nArgs:\n    reporting: - A CoreReporting or implementor of the same interface,\n        for error and progress reporting.\n\nReturns:\n    Tuple of:\n\n    sorted_indices - The indices of the metadata structures in\n        metadata_grouping, ordered by slice location\n\n    slice_thickness - A typical slice thickness for this group of\n        images\n\n    global_origin_mm - The coordinates of the first voxel in the image\n        volume\n\n    sorted_positions - The ImagePositionPatient for\n        each slice in the sorted"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Store a set of Dicom metadata structures, corresponding\nto a coherent sequence of images\n\nCreated by the DicomGrouper class, which separates and groups images into\ncoherent sequences according to their metadata."]}, {"name": "dicomity.group.DicomGrouper", "bases": ["UserList"], "methods": [{"name": "dicomity.group.DicomGrouper.add_item", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "metadata", "type": {"name": "GroupingMetadata", "xref": {"fqname": "dicomity.types.GroupingMetadata", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Add new metadata for an image. If the metadata is coherent with an\nexisting group, add the image to that group. Otherwise, create a new\ngroup.\n\nArgs:\n    filename: path to image\n    metadata: image metadata"]}, {"name": "dicomity.group.DicomGrouper.number_of_groups", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return the number of groups in this data"]}, {"name": "dicomity.group.DicomGrouper.get_stack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "index", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "DicomStack", "xref": {"fqname": "dicomity.group.DicomStack", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return a particular DicomStack"]}, {"name": "dicomity.group.DicomGrouper.largest_stack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "DicomStack", "xref": {"fqname": "dicomity.group.DicomStack", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Return the stack with the greatest number of images"]}, {"name": "dicomity.group.DicomGrouper.find_stack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "metadata", "type": {"name": "GroupingMetadata", "xref": {"fqname": "dicomity.types.GroupingMetadata", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "DicomStack", "xref": {"fqname": "dicomity.group.DicomStack", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Find a stack to which the specified image metadata can be added\n\nSearches for a DicomStack to which the new image metadata could be\nadded while forming a coherent image set. If no existing group exists,\ncreate and return a new empty group\n\nArgs:\n    metadata: image metadata\n\nReturns:\n    The DicomStack to which the image metadata belongs, or a new group"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Separate a series of Dicom images into groups of coherent images\n\nDicomGrouper splits a series of Dicom images into 'groups' of images with\nsimilar orientations and image properties. For example, a series containing\na scout image will typically be separated into a group containing the scan\nimages and another group containing the scout image. Similarly, a\nlocalizer series containing images in multiple orientations will typically\nbe separated into a separate group for each orientation."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "dicomity.load", "documentation": ["Functions for loading an image volume from DICOM files"], "functions": [{"name": "dicomity.load.load_main_image_from_dicom_files", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "image_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filenames", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reporting", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Loads a series of DICOM files into a coherent 3D volume\n\nArgs:\n    image_path: location of the DICOM files to load\n    filenames:\n    reporting: (Optional) An object implementing\n        Reporting for error, warning\n        and progress reporting. If no object is\n        provided then a default reporting object\n        is created.\n\nReturns:\n    Tuple of: image_wrapper, representative_metadata, slice_thickness,\n        global_origin_mm, sorted_positions\n\n    image: a np.array containing the 3D volume\n    representative_metadata: metadata from one slice of the main group\n    slice_thickness: the computed distance between centrepoints of each\n        slice\n    global_origin_mm: The mm coordinates of the image origin\n    sorted_positions: Patient positions for each slice in the sorted order"]}, {"name": "dicomity.load.load_metadata_from_dicom_files", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "image_path", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filenames", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "reporting", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "DicomGrouper", "xref": {"fqname": "dicomity.group.DicomGrouper", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Load metadata from a series of DICOM files\n\nArgs:\n    image_path: specify the location of the DICOM files.\n    filenames: filenames can be a string for a single filename, or an\n        array of strings\n    reporting: A CoreReporting or implementor of the same interface,\n        for error and progress reporting. Create a CoreReporting\n        with no arguments to hide all reporting. If no\n        reporting object is specified then a default\n        reporting object with progress dialog is\n        created\n\nReturns:\n    a DicomGrouper object containing the metadata grouped into coherent\n        sequences of images"]}, {"name": "dicomity.load.load_images_from_stack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "stack", "type": {"name": "DicomStack", "xref": {"fqname": "dicomity.group.DicomStack", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "reporting", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "np.array", "xref": {"fqname": "numpy.array", "project": "numpy"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Load metadata from a series of DICOM files\n\nArgs:\n    stack: a DicomStack containing metadata\n\n    reporting: (Optional) A Reporting or other implementor of\n        Reporting, for error and progress reporting.\n        Create a Reporting with no arguments to hide all reporting. If\n        no reporting object is specified then a default\n        reporting object with progress dialog is\n        created\n\nReturns:\n    a numpy array object containing the image volume"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dicomity.dictionary", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "dicomity.dictionary.DicomDictionary", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "dicomity.dictionary.DicomDictionary.__init__", "asynchronous